25, 1954. He then settled in Saegertown Pennsylvania and spent thirty-five years at Saegertown Manufacturing, retiring in 1996 as Plant Manager. He was a member of Christ Evangelical Free Church Saegertown for the second half of his life."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Fifty-nine year marriage, daughter predeceased him","body":"Robert married Ruth in 1953 — they were married for fifty-nine years until his death in 2012. Their daughter Cynthia Lybarger predeceased him at some point. He was also predeceased by his older brother Leroy 'Lee' Lybarger and his older sister Ruby Sheldon, leaving him survived only by oldest sister Ruth Watson and brother James in Texas."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"robert-lybarger-1930"},"I00678":{"id":"I00678","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Ruth","last_name":"Lybarger","married_names":[],"gender":"female","display_name":"Ruth Lybarger"},"birth":{"country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD4286","date_year":1953,"location_state":"Pennsylvania","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":2012,"children_ids":[]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["pennsylvania_migration"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"ruth-lybarger"},"HD4287":{"id":"HD428